Senior Software Engineer — Payments Platform
Brex · Remote (United States)
$185,000 – $225,000 + equity

About the role
We're hiring a Senior Software Engineer to help build and scale the core payments
platform that moves billions of dollars for thousands of businesses. You'll design
high-throughput, fault-tolerant backend services for authorization, ledgering, and money
movement, and partner closely with risk and compliance teams.

What you'll do
- Design and operate distributed backend services for real-time payment authorization and settlement.
- Build resilient ledger and reconciliation systems with strong consistency guarantees.
- Improve reliability, latency, and observability of payment-critical services.
- Integrate with card networks, banking partners, and third-party payment processors.
- Mentor engineers and drive technical design reviews.

What we're looking for
- 6+ years building backend services at scale, ideally in fintech or payments.
- Strong skills in a modern backend language (Go, Java, or Kotlin) and distributed systems.
- Experience with event-driven architectures, Kafka, and relational databases (PostgreSQL).
- Familiarity with cloud infrastructure (AWS), Kubernetes, and CI/CD.
- A track record of shipping reliable, high-throughput systems.

Nice to have
- Experience with double-entry ledgers, idempotency, and exactly-once processing.
- Exposure to PCI compliance and financial regulations.

Fully remote within the US. Must be authorized to work in the United States.